# Serialization Compatibility Integrity

## Must
- Preserve versioned schema contract and semantic version policy from `material-schema.md`.
- Validate backward/forward compatibility expectations for each schema change.
- Include integrity checks (checksums/lineage) for promoted baseline artifacts.
- Provide migration tooling notes for major layout or chunk changes.

## Must Not
- Do not change binary layout silently in policy-protected paths.
- Do not promote baselines with broken lineage or checksum mismatch.

## Required Evidence
- Serialization compatibility report and integrity verification artifact.
